28:00.972 --> 28:17.389
well look around and and see if we couldn't carry 
some American citizens to share the experience.

28:24.011 --> 28:42.071
The charter of NASA under the Space Act of 1958 is 
sufficiently broad to allow us to do things like

28:24.011 --> 28:42.071
this, with the justification being the 
dissemination of knowledge and the advancement

28:24.011 --> 28:42.071
of technology and the state of the art in the space 
program. And it was more a matter of determining

28:44.434 --> 28:47.477
how you would select people like this so that the 
American public was generally supportive of the

28:48.149 --> 29:08.832
fact that Mrs. so-and-so or Mr. so-and-so or Dr. 
somebody or other was going up instead of

28:48.149 --> 29:08.832
wondering why in the world the agency picked a 
person like that. The system was set up to allow us

29:10.273 --> 29:18.122
to carry journalists poets, artists, executives 
or managers from private industry, as well as the

29:18.625 --> 29:29.000
middle levels of the government, educators. And 
with Mr. Reagan's selection of an educator,

29:29.020 --> 29:47.788
secondary

29:29.020 --> 29:47.788
school or elementary teacher, which is his call as 
the chief executive to be the first one, gave the

29:29.020 --> 29:47.788
program 100% green light. We're looking forward 
to seeing somebody in about a year to come fly with

29:49.135 --> 29:53.720
us. Will they have to go through a certain program 
to get ready for the flight? Yeah. We don't think

29:58.685 --> 30:04.451
it'll be a very elaborate program, probably about 
two months or maybe a little longer. One of the

30:05.872 --> 30:16.223
primary things you would like to assure yourself 
of in any sort of training program like this is that

30:05.872 --> 30:16.223
in the event that there is some sort of a a crisis 
situation on board the shuttle. That individual

30:19.317 --> 30:36.101
